{
  "stem": "9665.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the one song which I didn't hear was the I didn't hear that one, but all the other ones, they were holding up their arms.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was happy that I left school in 1937.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, I did not have any friends, because I think that there might have been only one or two Jews among so many hundreds of others.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I still don't understand why my mother insisted I should go to that school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at the same time, I learned very well German, and I spoke already French because of Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Dutch was my mother's language, that wasn't a problem, so it helped me along the line.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did not experience that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was not-- I can't say that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Right, I met some of them after the war, or one in particular, and it was never-- it never was, you know, never mentioned to me that I was a Jew and they were Christians, or they were Nazis, or anything else.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But according to me, they were all pro-Hitler.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no doubt about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was involved in a Zionist organization.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how would I say-- camping on a Sunday, because on Shabbat I was not supposed to travel, in places like [GERMAN] and we left early in the morning by train, and we were all singing our Hebrew songs there.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Zionist organization was very strong in Holland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, the one which I like to mention, and that was in 1942, we went to Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I met there a number of friends, and one of them was Anne Frank.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she spoke Dutch with a very heavy German accent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This I remember very, very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
